      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative screws and rods from a single material lot. Sample size provides 80% power to detect a 10% QoI difference at alpha=0.05 based on observed coefficient of variation of 4.2%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions or rationale provided for single condition.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load angle (compression-bending per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry only). Torsion and tension-bending modes not tested in this COU. Rationale: compression-bending is the governing failure mode per clinical literature; additional modes deferred to future COU. Factor achieved level below required; accepted given supporting clinical justification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
